    "causal_summary": "`handlers/memory-index.ts:684` calls `sweepOrphanIndexRows({ limit: 200 })` with no cursor; the function defaults cursor=0 and returns `nextCursor`, which is echoed in scan results but never persisted or fed back, so every scan re-checks the same ~200 lowest-id rows forever (report §2 Chain B; ledger L2, live-verified 🟢)",
